--prisma
.npx prisma init //create schema.prisma file
    .setup prisma DB connection in this case vercel(.env.local)w    
.npx prisma migrate dev --name init    //this create migration file on vercel DB
    .make shure you have .env file first.
.npx prisma generate//generate prisma client
.prisma clinet (db.ts)
    .must not be in lib folder. it should be in Util folder(new created folder)



==vercel deployment
    -create storage in vercel using 'Neon'
        -this will crate the DB in 'neon' and setup using vercel.
    -create .env in local and paste what vercel gives you
        .from Vercel, '.env' and 'prisma' Tab
        .NB don't push .env file to gitHub(vercel will pick it and there will be error)
        .add in .gitignore file
            .# local env files
                .env*.local
                .env*
    -for prisma use this URL, in schema.prisma file.
        .datasource db {
            provider = "postgresql"
            url      = env("POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL") 
            }
        .in package.json add    
            "scripts": {
                "dev": "next dev",
                "build": "next build",
                "start": "next start",
                "lint": "next lint",
                "postinstall": "prisma generate"
            },

    -Environment variables(Settings > Environment Variables.) vercel, what you use in local env and what vercel gives you.
       

    ==Domain name
    1-To connect the domain waitingwall.com to Vercel, update your domainâ€™s nameservers to the following:
        ns1.vercel-dns.com
        ns2.vercel-dns.com

    2-Add the domain to your Vercel project:
        .in project , Settings > Domains > Add Domain
        .Enter your domain name (e.g., waitingwall.com)
        .Select the project you want to connect the domain to (production)
        .Click Add Domain

    3- Enable vercel Domain
        .out side project, click Domains Tab
        .edit the domain (waitingwall.com)
        .click Enable Domain
        